<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="1008" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1008">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/1664: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-30T15:00:00-04:00">May 30,
                                    1944—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>464. Department approves stand which you have taken regarding asylum as
                            reported in your 522, May 29, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>As, however, an Associated Press despatch dated 3:45 a.m. May 30, Quito,
                            reports that Arroyo del Río has taken refuge in the American Embassy,
                            the Department would appreciate an urgent clarifying report.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>